'''Robert "Bobby" Specht''' (October 22, 1921 â January 11, 1999 in [[Palm Springs, CA]]) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]] who competed in pairs and men's singles. He won the bronze medal in pairs with partner [[Joan Mitchell (figure skater)|Joan Mitchell]] at the [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] in 1941 and captured the gold in men's singles the following year. After serving in the Air Force during [[World War II]], he skated for many years with the [[Ice Capades]]
